This paper deals with data structures for storing and querying ordered trees with a given degree distribution. This topic falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects of trees, which could place it in the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) or graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the use of information theory in the analysis of the data structure could also make it relevant to the category of information theory (cs.IT).
